description: Feature-first JPA infrastructure responsibilities for the Spring Boot backend
globs: backend/src/**/java/**/infrastructure/**/*.java
alwaysApply: false
---

# Infrastructure Layer

- Put feature persistence adapters under `<feature>/infrastructure`.
- Keep only the feature's Spring Data repository in its infrastructure package.
- Do not create repository adapters, repository implementations, or duplicate persistence entities.
- The JPA repository persists the domain model directly.
- Every database repository uses Spring Data JPA.
- Spring Data interfaces extend `JpaRepository` and use `<Domain>JpaRepository`.
- Validate business constraints in the application service before calling a repository.
- Put shared technical configuration under `shared/infrastructure`.
- Put exception classes under `shared/infrastructure/exception`.
- Put `ApiError`, `GlobalExceptionHandler`, and other shared technical utilities under `shared/infrastructure/common`.
- Do not expose infrastructure persistence details through controllers or VOs.
